I think MC not going all out and tell everything is a reasonable choice because of various reasons:
1) Telling her about the group will inevitably lead to school authorities to know about it and punish everyone in it, including the MC. 
2) No one likes a snitch. If the group figures out MC snitched on them, he'll probably ended up in a very bad situation. 
3) They're childhood friends ffs. You mean to tell me that the girl didn't once consider the words of her childhood friend? Who probably know and care more about you than any other friends you have? Even if MC could have worded his warning better, she still should have at least listened to him.

Now I know that this group chat should be destroyed and doing so could save a lot of girls who might end up the same fate as FMC, but considering that MC is on the weaker side of males, I think his actions are at least better than FMC. While I also don't want to fully blame her for her actions, her fault is worse than MC. That is my judgement
